<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="1Aug1916"><font color="red">1/7 August 1916</font>, <cite>Pound/Joyce</cite> (Ezra Pound to JJ): Result is that he &ldquo;would consider&rdquo; publishing the Portrait with the Sequel, if the sequel could be inspected &ldquo;within reasonable time&rdquo;. He dont think the Portrait would pay by itself &hellip; Of course I am not waiting for *****, but if he could be started at the same time as Huebsch in New York, it would be a help. How much of Ulysses is done?</div>
